text:
Some horse tips
1. You can own up to 4 permanent horses 3 will be stabled plus the one you ride
2. Each stable sells different horses and new horses will unlock each chapter
3. While most stable horses are better than the ones you find in the wild there are several high quality wild horses you can find
4. There are 6 horse classes
Riding class: the lowest class with poor stats throughout 
Draft class: the slowest horses with the heaviest handling 
Race class: fast horses with poor health and stamina and will also spook easier with predators
War class: high health and stamina good in gunfights and braver with predators, average speed 
Work class: high stamina good health average speed good in gunfights and predators 
Superior class: statistically the best horses with the best handling but are very skittish around predators

text:
Tips for Gura:

1: You can switch your holstered weapons around now and have two revolvers instead of the shotgun. You can dual wield these for greater fire-power and you can buy more guns including duplicates of pistols from the gunsmith in town.

2: You can save an outfit from your dresser at camp or in a hotel and put it on your horse permanantly to switch back to if you ever lose your hat or neckwear.

3: Dead eye will eventually get an upgrade that lets you manually mark people with the fire button while time is slowed.

4: Talking to people and doing deeds will raise honor. Stealing and killing a towns worth of cops lowers it. Keep an eye on it and please try to get higher honor because the good ending of the game requires honor in the higher margin.
